Description: RNAS1_BISBI - Also known as RNS1. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Endonuclease that catalyzes the cleavage of RNA on the 3' side of pyrimidine nucleotides. Acts on single-stranded and double- stranded RNA (By similarity). From Bison bison (American bison) (Bos bison).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
